gomodel:SYNGO_2450  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Ephexin1 is phosphorylated by Cdk5-p35\"\nFig.7: \"Cdk5 phosphorylation of ephexin1 regulates EphA4-dependent GEF activity\"\n\nFig.8: \"Cdk5-dependent phosphorylation of ephexin1 is required for the ephrin-A1-mediated spine retraction\"\n- \"In ephexin1 knockdown neurons, however, ephrin-A1 did not reduce spine density (Fig. 8a-c). Similarly, ephrin-A1 did not reduce spine density in neurons from genetically ephexin1-deficient (ephexin1-/-; Ngef1-/-) neurons (Fig. 8d,e).\". Experimental description: Supplementary methods:\nPrimary cortical and hippocampal neurons were prepared from embryonic day\n18-19 rat embryos" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
